data.chText: 曲调；曲子
data.enText: a series of musical notes that are sung or played in a particular order to form a piece of music

data.chText: 他低声哼着一支熟悉的小曲。
data.enText: He was humming a familiar tune.

data.chText: 我不知道曲名，但听得出这曲调。
data.enText: I don't know the title but I recognize the tune.

data.chText: 这是一首悦耳易记的曲子。
data.enText: It was a catchy tune (= song) .

data.chText: 用《圣者的行进》的曲调唱的足球歌
data.enText: a football song sung to the tune of (= using the tune of) ‘When the saints go marching in’
be in/out of tune (with sb/sth)

data.chText: （与…）协调 / 不协调，一致 / 不一致，融洽 / 不融洽
data.enText: to be/not be in agreement with sb/sth; to have/not have the same opinions, feelings, interests, etc. as sb/sth

data.chText: 这些建议与我们在这个问题上的想法完全一致。
data.enText: These proposals are perfectly in tune with our own thoughts on the subject.

data.chText: 总统与公众舆论大唱反调。
data.enText: The President is out of tune with public opinion.
in/out of tune

data.chText: 音调正确 / 不正确；演奏合调 / 走调
data.enText: to be/not be singing or playing the correct musical notes to sound pleasant

data.chText: 他们中没有一个人能唱得合调。
data.enText: None of them could sing in tune.

data.chText: 钢琴弹得走调了。
data.enText: The piano is out of tune.
to the tune of sth

data.chText: （用于强调）总额达，总数为
data.enText: used to emphasize how much money sth has cost

data.chText: 这家旅馆重新装修花费达一百万元。
data.enText: The hotel has been refurbished to the tune of a million dollars.
call the shots/tune

data.chText: 控制；操纵
data.enText: to be the person who controls a situation
change your tune

data.chText: 改变调子；转变态度；变卦
data.enText: to express a different opinion or behave in a different way when your situation changes

data.chText: 等着瞧吧，到他遇上这事时，他很快就会改变调子了。
data.enText: Wait until it happens to him─he'll soon change his tune.
dance to sb's tune

data.chText: 听从某人的指挥；唯命是从；言听计从
data.enText: to do whatever sb tells you to
he who pays the piper calls the tune

data.chText: 花钱的人说了算；财大者气粗
data.enText: the person who provides the money for sth can also control how it is spent
sing a different tune

data.chText: 改变观点（或态度）；改弦易辙
data.enText: to change your opinion about sb/sth or your attitude towards sb/sth

data.chText: （为乐器）调音，校音
data.enText: to adjust a musical instrument so that it plays at the correct pitch

data.chText: 给吉他调弦
data.enText: to tune a guitar

data.chText: 调整，调节（发动机）
data.enText: to adjust an engine so that it runs smoothly and as well as possible

data.chText: （给收音机、电视等）调谐，调频道
data.enText: to adjust the controls on a radio or television so that you can receive a particular programme or channel

data.chText: 收音机调到了英国广播公司国际广播电台。
data.enText: The radio was tuned (in) to the BBC World Service.

data.chText: 别转台，下面的新闻马上就来。
data.enText: Stay tuned for the news coming up next.

data.chText: 调整；使协调；使适合
data.enText: to prepare or adjust sth so that it is suitable for a particular situation

data.chText: 他在演讲中专讲听众爱听的话。
data.enText: His speech was tuned to what the audience wanted to hear.
tune in (to sth)

data.chText: 收听（收音机广播节目）；收看（电视节目）
data.enText: to listen to a radio programme or watch a television programme
tune in to sb/sth

data.chText: 理解，体谅（他人的思想感情等）
data.enText: to become aware of other people's thoughts and feelings, etc.
tune out

data.chText: 不理睬；思想开小差
data.enText: to stop listening to sth

data.chText: 在她开始谈她工作的时候，他走神了。
data.enText: When she started talking about her job, he just tuned out.

trans: 调试，调整（发动机或机器）

tr: the adjustment of a radio receiver or other circuit to a required frequency
the property of producing accurately a note of a given pitch
example: the clarinet was out of tune

tr: a succession of notes forming a distinctive sequence
example: she was humming an air from Beethoven
My piano needs to be tuned

value.def: A tune is a series of musical notes that is pleasant and easy to remember.

example.ex: She was humming a merry little tune.
example.tran: 她正哼着一支欢快的小调。

value.def: You can refer to a song or a short piece of music as a tune .

example.ex: She'll also be playing your favourite pop tunes.
example.tran: 她还将演奏你最喜欢的流行乐曲。

value.def: When someone tunes a musical instrument, they adjust it so that it produces the right notes.

example.ex: 'We do tune our guitars before we go on,' he insisted.
example.tran: “我们在演奏以前确实会为吉他调音，”他坚持说道。

example.ex: Others were quietly tuning up their instruments.
example.tran: 其他人正静静地为他们的乐器调音。

value.def: When an engine or machine is tuned, it is adjusted so that it works well.

example.ex: Drivers are urged to make sure that car engines are properly tuned.
example.tran: 司机们被敦促要确保汽车发动机调试妥当。

example.ex: The shop charges up to $500 to tune up a Porsche.
example.tran: 那家店调试一辆保时捷收费高达 500 美元。

value.tran: 调试，调整(发动机或机器)

value.def: If your radio or television is tuned to a particular broadcasting station, you are listening to or watching the programmes being broadcast by that station.

example.ex: A small colour television was tuned to an afternoon soap opera.
example.tran: 一台小彩色电视机频道调在了一出下午的肥皂剧上。

value.def: If you say that a person or organization is calling the tune, you mean that they are in a position of power or control in a particular situation.

example.ex: Who would then be calling the tune in Parliament?

value.def: If you say that someone has changed their tune, you are criticizing them because they have changed their opinion or way of doing things.

example.ex: You've changed your tune since this morning, haven't you?...
example.tran: 你从今天早上就变卦了，是不是？

example.ex: Yesterday he changed his tune, saying the fare increase was experimental.
example.tran: 昨天他变卦了，说提价只是试行。

value.tran: 改变调子;变卦;改变态度

value.def: If you say that someone is dancing to someone else's tune, you mean that they are allowing themselves to be controlled by the other person.

example.ex: The danger of commercialism is that the churches end up dancing to the tune of their big business sponsors.
example.tran: 商业主义的危险就是教会最终可能会被大赞助商牵着鼻子走。

value.tran: 被…牵着鼻子走;受…的控制

value.def: A person or musical instrument that is in tune produces exactly the right notes. A person or musical instrument that is out of tune does not produce exactly the right notes.

example.ex: It was just an ordinary voice, but he sang in tune...
example.tran: 他声音很一般，但唱得都在调子上。

example.ex: Many of the notes are out of tune...
It's no wonder the piano kept going out of tune.
example.tran: 难怪钢琴一直不在调上。

value.tran: 合调的/走调的;在调子上/不在调子上

value.def: If you are in tune with a group of people, you are in agreement or sympathy with them. If you are out of tune with them, you are not in agreement or sympathy with them.

example.ex: Today, his change of direction seems more in tune with the times...
example.tran: 今天，他方向的改变似乎更与时代合拍。

example.ex: The peace campaigners were probably out of tune with most Britons.
example.tran: 和平倡导者可能不被大部分英国人认同。

value.tran: 一致/不一致;赞同/不赞同

value.def: To the tune of a particular amount of money means to the extent of that amount.

example.ex: They've been sponsoring the World Cup to the tune of a million and a half pounds.
example.tran: 他们已经对世界杯提供了高达 150 万英镑的赞助费。

xrse.def: he who pays the piper calls the tune
